This is the moment six members of the crew on a cargo ship were plucked to safety as their vessel sank in the English Channel.

A mayday was sent at around 7am today as the engine room started to flood on the Sea Breeze coaster, which was 11 miles south-east of The Lizard in Cornwall.

Royal National Lifeboat Institution boats, coastguards and a search and rescue helicopter were sent to the scene and attempts were made to pump the water from the 285ft ship.

