A Royal Navy offshore patrol ship, HMS Tyne, was also despatched because it had bigger pumps.

But an hour after the arrival of rescuers the decision was taken to abandon the vessel which was carrying limestone.

Alex Greig, Falmouth Coastguard Watch Manager, said the crew were taken on board a lifeboat and were in good health apart from a few cuts and grazes.

He said: ‘We received the mayday broadcast from the Sea Breeze at 7am and were able to get lifeboats and the helicopter on scene quickly, along with other vessels that were in the vicinity.

